* Surrendering at a police station or courthouse with their attorney
* Being placed under house arrest or electronic monitoring

* An arrest warrant being issued but not executed
* Being questioned or interviewed without arrest
* Being named in an indictment without arrest

JD Vance is scheduled to deliver remarks on the One Big Beautiful Bill Act at a steel fabrication facility in La Crosse, Wisconsin, on August 28. More here: https://www.jsonline.com/story/news/politics/2025/08/26/jd-vance-coming-to-wisconsin-to-tout-the-one-big-beautiful-bill/85823534007/

This market will resolve to "Yes" if JD Vance says the listed term during his appearance at this event. Otherwise, it will resolve to "No."

Any usage of the term, regardless of context, will count toward the resolution of this market.

Pluralization or possessive forms of the term will count, but other variations will not count.

Instances where the term appears in a compound word will count regardless of context (e.g., joyful is not a compound of "joy," but killjoy is).

If "President Trump" is mentioned, it will count as one mention for the "Trump / President 30+ times" market.

This market applies only to the scheduled remarks on August 28. Speeches, events, or comments outside of this event will not qualify. If the event includes a Q&A session, those remarks will also count toward resolution.

If the event is definitively cancelled, or not aired by August 28, 2025, at 11:59 PM ET, this market will resolve to "No."

The resolution source will be the audio/video of the listed event.
